	   <tr><td colspan=2>I did not discover this till lvl 16 and had considered bolts not worth the trouble till then.&nbsp;&nbsp;That is the main advantage of bolts is that they have a 300 foot range instead of a 200 foot like most spells.  My favorite lvl 16 tactic is to cast sheldskin which absorbs 55? hit points, cast invisible on myself, walk around till i find the perfect target, measure out 300 feet as best i can.  Hit it with a lightnig bolt for 108 damabe, as it runs toward me hit it with flame shock for 102?  If both spells are unresisted the target reaches me with 200+ hitpoints gone, and I have 55 extra hp.  Which you need cuz with each lvl your melee skills fall further and further behind the targets you typically attack.  I have killed a couple of yellows this way, something I haven't done since lvl 3.  Most yellows I end up running from even with a 250+ hp head start, so I only take them on when I'm near someplace safe I can run to.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
