	   <tr><td colspan=2>The only skill you have left to learn as a wizzie is dodge at 22.&nbsp;&nbsp;Magic skills are easily enough increased by sitting around practicing somewhere, language skills by sitting around talking to your groupmates, and combat skills should not be a concern at this point (If you are still meleeing, dump your finger-wiggler and start a tank.)  After putting 1 point into each of your specialization skills, I'd use the rest to get your research up, or a trade skill.<br><br>When you hit 22, put 1 point into Dodge, and then just start putting your points wherever you want.  I wouldn't point more than 1 point into Dodge.  It's very easy to increase.  Just go stand in the middle of the small orc camp in East Commonlands.  Your skill will increase rapidly, and the campers will love the fact that the orcs ignore them even though they are the ones doing the damage (your level and the faction hits you took when YOU were camping the orcs make you the preferred target).  I put up my shield and leatherskin, and my skill was up a good 10 points before I took even 1 point of damage.  But then, I soloed a great deal so my combat skills were already up fairly high (at 29 offense, defense, and piercing are all over 100).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
