	   <tr><td colspan=2>Trust me, the best possible thing you can do with your training points is to save them until you are able to do Research.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then everytime you level pump the maximum amount of training points you can into Research, this way you will rarely ever fail at making new spells, and you won't be wasting those ever precious runes that are sometimes so hard to find.<br><br>Don't waste training points on anything else, Research is by far the most valuable skill you can pump them into for a wizard.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
